This paper deals with the design and analysis of a protocol for ad hoc networks, which is a topic typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and utility maximization, which are common themes in the information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The use of stochastic geometry to analyze the performance of the protocol suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the mathematical aspects (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses fairness in medium access, which is a topic that falls under the game theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
